In the District Court for the third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding terms at Seattle for the County of King:

The above named cause coming on before me in chambers upon the petition of Michael Hennan complaining that he is illegaly restrained of his liberty by J.H. McGraw the Sheriff and Jailer of said County of King, and praying for a summons to issue for the persons of any and all witnesses against the said Henan to appear before me at a certain time and place certain, wherin and wherefore I might inquire into the said restraint to ascertain if such restraint be illegal:

NOW THEN this is to order that you J.H. McGraw Sheriff and jailer of the said county of King as aforesaid do produce at two o'clock of the afternoon of the 22d. day of August 1885 before me at my chambers of the Court Hoise of said King County the bofy of the said Michael Henan and there you be to answer why and wherefore such Henan be restained and have you then and there - this writ and your return thereon; and you do summon to appear before me at the same time and place aforesaid directed Elizabeth Pritehard, Jacob Levy, Chas E. Harding, F.C. Bird, Thos. Morse, Helen Walsh, D.W. Ricard and J.H. Woolery to testify and make known their cause against the said Heenan and why he is so restrained as aforesaid:-
And I do order that a writ in compliance with this order do issue from the hand and seal of the clerk of the above named Court commanding you as aforesaid to be and appear.
Dated at Seattle King County this 21st. day of August A.D. 1885 Roger S. Greene Judge of said Court.
In the District Court, Third Judicial District, holding terms at Seattle, Washington Territory.
In re application of Michael Henan for a Writ of Habeas Corpus - JH McGraw
FILED AUG 21 1885 James Seavey, Clerk. By James Ludlow, Deputy Clerk.
